Citation.sAbstract: This work reports new density data (180 points) of 1-hexanol at twelve different temperatures between 293.15 and 403.15 K (every 10 K), and fifteen different pressures from 0.1 to 140 MPa (every 10 MPa). An Anton Paar vibrating tube densimeter, calibrated with an uncertainty of +/- 0.5 kg m-3 was used to  perform these measurements. The experimental density data were fitted with the Tait-like equation with low standard deviations. In addition, the isobaric thermal expansivity and the isothermal compressibility were derived from the Tait-like equation.
Citation.sTitle: Liquid density of oxygenated additives to bio-fuels: 1-Hexanol at pressures up to 140 MPa and from 293.15 K to 403.15 K
